 <body>
  <h1>
   <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Data_Structures/i_DS_Clear_Grid.png"/><br/>
   Clear Grid
  </h1>
  With this action you can clear a grid data structure to a single value (each cell within the grid will be set to the value given). You supply the variable that holds the grid index (as returned by the action
  <a href="Create_Grid.htm">
   Create Grid
  </a>
  )
    and then give the value to clear the grid to.
  <h4>
   Action Syntax:
  </h4>
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Data_Structures/a_DS_Clear_Grid.png"/><br/>
  <h4>
   Arguments:
  </h4>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      Grid
     </td>
     <td>
      The index (stored in a variable) of the grid to clear
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      Value
     </td>
     <td>
      The value to clear the grid to
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Data_Structures/e_DS_Clear_Grid.png"/><br/>
  The above action block code clears the given grid data structure to hold the keyword
  <span>
   noone
  </span>
  in
    each cell if a global variable is less than or equal to 0.
 </body>
</html>